{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/blog/js-kongress-2019-revolution-of-architectures","result":{"data":{"sanityPost":{"title":"JS Kongress 2019 - Revolution of Architectures","_rawBody":[{"_key":"bc37e306656b","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"bc37e306656b0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Takeaways from a great Javascript and Frontend conference in Munich"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h2"},{"_key":"f6de287bdc73","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"f6de287bdc730","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"This is one of the conferences that I try to attend every year because it is organized by the local community and attracts also great many international developers and speakers. "}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"f748a9df7595","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"f748a9df75950","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"I am really happy that we are getting more and more interesting conferences here -> I am looking at you "},{"_key":"f748a9df75951","_type":"span","marks":["bdd1d27ee5f3"],"text":"@btconf"},{"_key":"f748a9df75952","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" and "},{"_key":"f748a9df75953","_type":"span","marks":["2242aa800a5f"],"text":"JSCraftCamp"},{"_key":"f748a9df75954","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" ... only to mention the first two that popped in my mind."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"bdd1d27ee5f3","_type":"link","href":"https://twitter.com/btconf"},{"_key":"2242aa800a5f","_type":"link","href":"https://twitter.com/JSCraftCamp"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"aa63dcab28e4","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"aa63dcab28e40","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"But back to "},{"_key":"aa63dcab28e41","_type":"span","marks":["9239cacf1ba2"],"text":"JSKongress"},{"_key":"aa63dcab28e42","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" 2019:"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"9239cacf1ba2","_type":"link","href":"https://twitter.com/JSKongress"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"ca866b76dbec","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"ca866b76dbec0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"There were many good talks and presentations and an exceptionally interesting "},{"_key":"ca866b76dbec1","_type":"span","marks":["strong"],"text":"deep track "},{"_key":"ca866b76dbec2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"(open space / bof)"},{"_key":"ca866b76dbec3","_type":"span","marks":["strong"],"text":" "},{"_key":"ca866b76dbec4","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"with e.g. the maintainers of #webpack and #rollup."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"c15661535bc2","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c15661535bc20","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"I could spend the whole day talking about the many interesting topics, but I wanted to pick out the two that did not let me stop thinking and led to the beginnings of my current endeavour of a Github project for a Microfrontend Architecture Solution, but more about that later.."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"a3aaf582076e","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"a3aaf582076e0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Talk 01: Independent deployment of the frontend with Docker and Kubernetes"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"1f53050deeab","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"1f53050deeab0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"by "},{"_key":"1f53050deeab1","_type":"span","marks":["ccd0be18bba9"],"text":"@monicalent"},{"_key":"1f53050deeab2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"ccd0be18bba9","_type":"link","href":"https://twitter.com/monicalent"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"f3eda9f02efa","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"f3eda9f02efa0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"She talked about the benefits and complications of independently maintaining and deploying parts of a frontend and showcased a solution that integrated with Docker and Kubernetes. This is a nice way of solving the CI and DevOps part of the whole Microfrontend idea."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"bd968e8b0362","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"bd968e8b03620","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Read more here: "},{"_key":"bd968e8b03621","_type":"span","marks":["f5772ae1df2f"],"text":"https://js-kongress.com/sessions/independent-deployment-of-the-frontend-with-docker-and-kubernetes/"},{"_key":"bd968e8b03622","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"f5772ae1df2f","_type":"link","href":"https://js-kongress.com/sessions/independent-deployment-of-the-frontend-with-docker-and-kubernetes/"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"9498303a3572","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"9498303a35720","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Talk 02: Angular, React, Vue and Co. â€“ peacefully united thanks to Web Components and Micro Apps"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"fe136ee2dd5b","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"fe136ee2dd5b0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"by "},{"_key":"fe136ee2dd5b1","_type":"span","marks":["81a6584d301e"],"text":"@ManfredSteyer"},{"_key":"fe136ee2dd5b2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"81a6584d301e","_type":"link","href":"https://twitter.com/manfredsteyer"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"f2a52b722600","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"f2a52b7226000","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"He talked about decomposing a big solution into small self-contained parts that can be maintained by different teams and that way microservices in the backend have their siblings in the frontend with micro apps..."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"61dcc30874e9","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"61dcc30874e90","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Read more here: "},{"_key":"61dcc30874e91","_type":"span","marks":["fa23a54613e1"],"text":"https://js-kongress.com/sessions/angular-react-vue-and-co-peacefully-united-thanks-to-web-components-and-micro-apps/"},{"_key":"61dcc30874e92","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"fa23a54613e1","_type":"link","href":"https://js-kongress.com/sessions/angular-react-vue-and-co-peacefully-united-thanks-to-web-components-and-micro-apps/"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"0a960ade25a8","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"0a960ade25a80","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Hopefully the slides and video recording of the conference are soon online, so you can also participate after the fact"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"7b1b38fc5504","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"7b1b38fc55040","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Interesting - I want to know more....."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"bfd499455f73","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"bfd499455f730","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"One of the resources that describes the concept very well is the site "},{"_key":"bfd499455f731","_type":"span","marks":["44edcf165c38"],"text":"https://micro-frontends.org/"},{"_key":"bfd499455f732","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" and I compiled a list of youtube videos of different speakers that talk about their experiences in actually implementing such a solution and what challenges and pitfalls they faced: "},{"_key":"bfd499455f733","_type":"span","marks":["6ca527df20b8"],"text":"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1qIp0pQfjQ1q_Hb42IBvVQNt0WVrZXrG"},{"_key":"bfd499455f734","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"44edcf165c38","_type":"link","href":"https://micro-frontends.org/"},{"_key":"6ca527df20b8","_type":"link","href":"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1qIp0pQfjQ1q_Hb42IBvVQNt0WVrZXrG"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"b45113d92df0","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b45113d92df00","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"As I mentioned in the beginning, I started developing a Proof Of Concept and a library that can be used to orchestrate a microfrontend solution with a little help of GraphQL as the common language to let the parts in the loosely coupled frontend and backend communicate and also share state if needed."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"6c8b29904815","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"6c8b299048150","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Disclaimer: it is in the very early stages and under heavy development, but I wanted to give other people the chance to discuss and contribute early on. Look for yourself: "},{"_key":"6c8b299048151","_type":"span","marks":["ef8dd08ab7ec"],"text":"https://github.com/microfront/microfront"},{"_key":"6c8b299048152","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"ef8dd08ab7ec","_type":"link","href":"https://github.com/microfront/microfront"}],"style":"normal"}],"heroImage":{"asset":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.910828025477707,"src":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=1080&h=565&fit=crop","srcSet":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=270&h=141&fit=crop 270w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=540&h=283&fit=crop 540w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=1080&h=565&fit=crop 1080w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png 1200w","srcWebp":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=1080&h=565&fit=crop&fm=webp","srcSetWebp":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=270&h=141&fit=crop&fm=webp 270w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=540&h=283&fit=crop&fm=webp 540w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?w=1080&h=565&fit=crop&fm=webp 1080w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/q8ly2id8/production/028e1a54795ed90840daee0512ef040b86c115fc-1200x628.png?fm=webp 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"js-kongress-2019-revolution-of-architectures"}}}